name: Intaki Cycle of Ida Bracelet
description: A silver bracelet. The outer surface of the band is worked with a representation of two Intaki serpent fish, chasing each other in a circle. The hidden inner surface shows one serpent fish eating the other while laying a trail of roe behind it. The Ida way of life emphasizes the cycle of life, death, and rebirth, as does this fine silver bracelet.
